 al. 2003; Howe et al. 2017). &nbsp;The cholesterol synthesis pathway involves a number of precursor molecules and enzymes (Sakakura et al. 2001; Itkonen et al. 2023).  Table 1: List of cholesterol synthesis enzymes with identifier of enzyme (Uniprot, 2024).           Enzyme    Identifier          Hydroxymethylglutaryl-CoA synthase    EC:2.3.3.10          Hydroxymethylglutaryl-CoA reductase    EC:1.1.1.34          Mevalonate kinase    EC:2.7.1.36          Phosphomevalonate kinase    EC:2.7.4.2          Diphosphomevalonate decarboxylase    EC:4.1.1.33          Isopentenyl-diphosphate Delta-isomerase    EC:5.3.3.2          Geranylgeranyl diphosphate synthase    EC 2.5.1.29          (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate synthase    EC:2.5.1.10          Squalene synthase    EC:2.5.1.21          Squalene monooxygenase    EC:1.14.14.17          Lanosterol synthase    EC:5.4.99.7          Sterol 14alpha-demethylase    EC:1.14.14.154          Delta(7)-sterol 5(6)-desaturase    EC:1.14.19.20          7-dehydrocholesterol reductase    EC:1.3.1.21", "timestamp": "Fri May 15 22:01:00 +0000 2026"}